<br>
None of the ones at the village (Lightfoots, Watchers and Provens) have pets.<br>
<br>
I have been doing these on and off for a few levels.  What I normally do is sit/med down near the cost by the single ogre spawn.  It's safe down there and you will not get wanderers while you med.<br>
<br>
When I'm ready I go down to the town and flux up 4 and run em over the water down to my med spot.  After that round em up and kill em.  Using circle of force I had to resnare after the 6th cast.  After that is was usually five or six more casts to take em all down.<br>
<br>
Tips:  Make sure you have lev and sow up (no brainer).  They are social so you can get adds on your pulls.  I wasn't able to consistantly split them with the staff untill about level 50.  So chances are if you flux one and another is close it will come as well.<br>
<br>
Don't panic if you get more than 4 just root one and continue on your way.  You can usually get far enough out of range that when root breaks it will go back.  Another reason I prefer to not snare them until farther down the beach.  <br>
<br>
Provens have alot of hps so if you arent sure of your mana pool I would single kite one using CoF, if it doesnt look like you can finish it with CoF only then stay away from those or root nuke em.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
